			<content translate="true">Communication is the method by which two or more people interact; therefore, it is essentially a social process.</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text02" x="375" y="80" width="341" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Babies communicate non-verbally long before they can talk and use words to express themselves. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Their ability to communicate effectively develops rapidly during the first few months and years of life. &lt;/P&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="text03" x="375" y="170" width="342" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">Researchers believe that:&lt;LI&gt;Our genetic foundation enables human beings to acquire language. &lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Children in particular must have powerful learning mechanisms to learn the specific properties of their own language.&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
